# Git branching

- Start every new feature, fix, or experiment on its own branch off `main` (e.g. `feature/ci`, `fix/load-bug`).
- Do not commit feature work directly on `main`.
- Do not pile unrelated work onto an existing feature branch — open a new branch instead.
- One pull request per branch.

When beginning implementation, create and checkout the branch before editing files.
